with love" argument?

242
00:10:53,887 --> 00:10:56,657
I should have
written that down.

243
00:10:57,524 --> 00:10:59,094
Look, Lily, I...

244
00:11:00,460 --> 00:11:01,560
I make more
money than you.

245
00:11:01,628 --> 00:11:02,858
Excuse me?

246
00:11:05,799 --> 00:11:07,429
Dance for me.

247
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:08,270
Oh, Marshall.

248
00:11:08,335 --> 00:11:09,835
Dude.

249
00:11:09,903 --> 00:11:12,073
It all made so much sense
when you said it,

250
00:11:12,139 --> 00:11:13,809
but when I said it,
it turned into a fight.

251
00:11:13,874 --> 00:11:15,384
And once Lily and
I start fighting,

252
00:11:15,442 --> 00:11:19,752
the fight starts to
mutate and multiply.

253
00:11:19,813 --> 00:11:22,123
MARSHALL:
Sure, it started with
the dishes, but then...

254
00:11:22,182 --> 00:11:25,222
So you're saying
that you shouldn't
have to wash dishes

255
00:11:25,285 --> 00:11:27,285
because you work
harder than me?

256
00:11:27,354 --> 00:11:30,694
Okay, that's not what
I'm saying, but it's true.

257
00:11:30,758 --> 00:11:31,888
MARSHALL:
And then all of a sudden,

258
00:11:31,959 --> 00:11:33,389
we're also fighting
about who works harder.

259
00:11:33,460 --> 00:11:35,160
I teach kindergarten.

260
00:11:35,228 --> 00:11:37,698
I am molding
the future leaders
of tomorrow.

261
00:11:37,765 --> 00:11:40,165
You eat cookies
and glue stuff.

262
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:41,873
MARSHALL:
And soon
more fights spin off.

263
00:11:41,935 --> 00:11:44,435
I can't believe
you'd rather be killed...

264
00:11:44,504 --> 00:11:46,114
MARSHALL: Until there are
more fights going on than
you can even keep track of.

265
00:11:46,173 --> 00:11:48,213
LILY: If you need to go
in the middle of the night,

266
00:11:48,275 --> 00:11:51,035
either turn
the bathroom light on
or sit down.

267
00:11:51,111 --> 00:11:53,551
MARSHALL: My mother
does not hate you.

268
00:11:53,613 --> 00:11:55,953
She is neutral about you.

269
00:11:56,016 --> 00:11:58,786
I am not scared of
your Shining impression.

270
00:11:58,852 --> 00:12:02,022
I just don't need to hear it,
especially at night.

271
00:12:02,089 --> 00:12:05,529
"Danny's not here,
Mrs. Torrance."

272
00:12:05,592 --> 00:12:07,232
Please don't do that.

273
00:12:08,495 --> 00:12:10,895
Man, Lily fights dirty.

274
00:12:10,964 --> 00:12:14,204
She's small but vicious,
like a badger

275
00:12:14,267 --> 00:12:15,967
that your brothers caught
and starved for five days

276
00:12:16,036 --> 00:12:18,936
and then put in
your sleeping bag.

277
00:12:19,006 --> 00:12:20,906
I should just go home
and apologize.

278
00:12:20,974 --> 00:12:24,484
No. What you need
is a surge. Fight harder.

279
00:12:26,046 --> 00:12:28,246
Picture it, Marshall,

280
00:12:28,315 --> 00:12:30,015
never having to
wash another dish
as long as you live,

281
00:12:30,083 --> 00:12:32,653
yet all the dishes
are always clean.

282
00:12:32,719 --> 00:12:36,019
Why, this would
take all the anxiety
out of snacking.

283
00:12:36,089 --> 00:12:38,489
No more holding
open your shirt

284
00:12:38,558 --> 00:12:41,158
to form a makeshift bowl
for your salty treats.

285
00:12:41,228 --> 00:12:43,528
That world is yours,
Marshall.

286
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:48,866
Reach out, take it.
Dip it in some
ranch dressing, enjoy.

287
00:12:52,472 --> 00:12:54,312
He's right.
No!

288
00:12:54,374 --> 00:12:56,344
Barney's stupid ideas
are what got you
into this quagmire.

289
00:12:56,409 --> 00:12:58,609
There's no exit strategy.
Just wash your stupid dishes.

290
00:12:58,678 --> 00:13:00,848
No! Those dishes
are my manhood.

291
00:13:00,914 --> 00:13:03,584
And if I want to
leave my manhood
dirty in the sink,

292
00:13:03,650 --> 00:13:05,720
caked with ketchup
and pasta...
What are you eating?

293
00:13:05,785 --> 00:13:08,115
...then damn it,
that's my right!

294
00:13:08,188 --> 00:13:10,888
I'll wash my manhood
when I'm good and ready!

295
00:13:11,691 --> 00:13:12,561
Where was he not sitting?

296
00:13:14,127 --> 00:13:17,157
Hmm. Hey, Barnstormer.
Hey, Ro-Ro.

297
00:13:17,230 --> 00:13:18,970
Ooh!

298
00:13:19,032 --> 00:13:21,002
Okay, now you have
adorable nicknames?

299
00:13:21,068 --> 00:13:22,938
Seriously,
what's going on
with you two?

300
00:13:23,003 --> 00:13:25,143
Nothing.
We're just happy.

301
00:13:25,205 --> 00:13:28,205
It's like Gandhi said,
"Smile don't cost
nothing, sugar."

302
00:13:28,275 --> 00:13:31,105
I'm not sure you know
who Gandhi is.

303
00:13:31,178 --> 00:13:32,808
So, Ted, did you talk
to our neighbors?

304
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:37,520
Yes, yeah, I did.
I went up there ready
to set them straight.

305
00:13:37,584 --> 00:13:38,524
(BAGPIPES PLAYING)

306
00:13:40,420 --> 00:13:41,320
(BAGPIPES STOP)

307
00:13:48,295 --> 00:13:49,495
They're old?

308
00:13:49,562 --> 00:13:50,462
Really old.

309
00:13:51,564 --> 00:13:53,074
So what did you do?

310
00:13:53,133 --> 00:13:54,673
Well, I didn't have the heart
to tell them to stop,

311
00:13:54,734 --> 00:13:56,474
because, well,
good for them.

312
00:13:56,536 --> 00:13:59,736
So I just welcomed
them to the building,
had a hard candy,

313
00:13:59,806 --> 00:14:02,306
nodded politely
at some racist comments
and then left.

314
00:14:04,344 --> 00:14:06,514
OLDER TED:
Over the next couple of days,

315
00:14:06,579 --> 00:14:09,279
Barney and Robin
continued to be
happier than ever.

316
00:14:09,349 --> 00:14:11,049
And Marshall and Lily
continued to fight.

317
00:14:11,118 --> 00:14:15,718
I don't care
if the dishes aren't done.
Okay, if you care, you do it.

318
00:14:15,788 --> 00:14:18,988
Great. Then I don't care
if you have an orgasm.

319
00:14:19,059 --> 00:14:21,159
If you care, you do it.

320
00:14:21,228 --> 00:14:24,628
I went 18 years
without the touch
of a woman.

321
00:14:24,697 --> 00:14:25,797
I can do it again.

322
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:27,595
You might have to.

323
00:14:27,667 --> 00:14:30,137
(BAGPIPES PLAYING)

324
00:14:30,203 --> 00:14:31,873
OLDER TED: And I continued
to hear more bagpiping than
the St. Paddy's Day parade.

325
00:14:36,910 --> 00:14:39,710
I don't know what to do.
Lily and I have never
had a fight this long.

326
00:14:39,779 --> 00:14:41,309
It's like
I don't even exist.

327
00:14:41,381 --> 00:14:44,721
On Sunday morning,
she made pancake, Ted.

328
00:14:44,784 --> 00:14:47,624
Pancake and bacon strip.

329
00:14:47,687 --> 00:14:52,457
It's your own fault.
You took relationship
advice from Barney.

330
00:14:52,525 --> 00:14:53,825
Well, maybe Barney
has it all figured out.

331
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:55,263
(TED SCOFFS)

332
00:14:55,328 --> 00:14:58,028
He and Ro-Ro are
the best couple now.

333
00:14:58,098 --> 00:14:59,298
Lily and I have
been dethroned.

334
00:14:59,366 --> 00:15:01,096
You know what,
I'm not buying it.

335
00:15:01,168 --> 00:15:04,098
All that cutesy,
lovey-dovey crap,
that's not them.

336
00:15:04,171 --> 00:15:07,011
And I know for a fact
that Robin hates nicknames.

337
00:15:08,908 --> 00:15:10,278
Thanks, Robbsy-wobbsy.

338
00:15:10,343 --> 00:15:13,583
Yeah, I don't do nicknames.

339
00:15:13,646 --> 00:15:15,076
Finished with
the sports page,
Sherbs?

340
00:15:15,148 --> 00:15:16,548
Seriously, stop.

341
00:15:18,818 --> 00:15:21,218
Hey, Robin, it's T-Mose.

342
00:15:21,288 --> 00:15:24,058
Yeah, I don't like
them on you, either.

343
00:15:24,124 --> 00:15:25,634
Well, she obviously
likes them now.

344
00:15:25,692 --> 00:15:30,002
And come on,
somebody had to put
an end to T-Mose.

345
00:15:30,063 --> 00:15:33,473
No, T-Mose was awesome.

346
00:15:33,533 --> 00:15:35,573
I'm thinking of
bringing it back.

347
00:15:35,635 --> 00:15:38,405
(BAGPIPES PLAYING)

348
00:15:38,471 --> 00:15:41,771
Bagpiping sounds
a little different today.
It's all echo-y.

349
00:15:41,841 --> 00:15:43,941
Yeah. They're in
the bathroom.

350
00:15:44,011 --> 00:15:46,311
I think they're bagpiping
on the shower chair.

351
00:15:46,379 --> 00:15:48,849
OLDER TED:
And just like that,

352
00:15:48,915 --> 00:15:50,815
I realized exactly
how to get the real scoop
on Barney and Robin.

353
00:15:50,883 --> 00:15:52,623
Hey, Ted.
How are Marshall and Lily?

354
00:15:52,685 --> 00:15:54,415
I worry about those two,
I really do.

355
00:15:54,487 --> 00:15:56,817
You and your big,
giant heart.

356
00:15:56,889 --> 00:15:59,229
Okay, enough.
The jig is up.

357
00:16:00,427 --> 00:16:02,527
Ted, whatever
do you mean?

358
00:16:02,595 --> 00:16:03,655
Who's this guy?

359
00:16:03,730 --> 00:16:04,960
We'll get to that.

360
00:16:05,032 --> 00:16:06,632
You see, I knew
something was wrong.

361
00:16:06,699 --> 00:16:10,969
You two were too happy,
too shiny, too nickname-y.

362
00:16:11,038 --> 00:16:12,408
Didn't add up.

363
00:16:12,472 --> 00:16:15,542
You two never fight?
Horse apples.

364
00:16:15,608 --> 00:16:19,308
You fight all the time.

365
00:16:20,913 --> 00:16:21,913
How would
you know that?

366
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:23,551
Phil told me.

367
00:16:23,616 --> 00:16:25,216
Who the hell is Phil?

368
00:16:25,285 --> 00:16:26,785
Your downstairs neighbor.

369
00:16:26,853 --> 00:16:30,993
Hi. I'm Phil. 12 B.

370
00:16:31,058 --> 00:16:33,488
And he's heard
everything.

371
00:16:39,499 --> 00:16:42,169
So Phil tells me that Ro-Ro
and the Barnstormer

372
00:16:42,235 --> 00:16:45,635
have been fighting a lot.
Care to explain?

373
00:16:48,475 --> 00:16:50,005
(BOTH SIGHING)

374
00:16:50,077 --> 00:16:53,207
Okay. Everything
was going great.

375
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:55,750
Our no-fighting techniques
were working perfectly

376
00:16:55,815 --> 00:16:57,745
until we went
on that ski trip
last weekend.

377
00:16:57,817 --> 00:16:59,787
Hmm.

378
00:16:59,852 --> 00:17:02,392
So I showed Marshall
that Lily's argument
was bananas

379
00:17:02,455 --> 00:17:04,615
and now
he'll never have to
wash another dish.

380
00:17:04,691 --> 00:17:06,161
High two.

381
00:17:06,226 --> 00:17:07,926
That's terrible advice.

382
00:17:07,994 --> 00:17:09,964
What? You agree
with Lily? You...

383
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:11,529
(CHAIR LIFT JAMS)

384
00:17:15,068 --> 00:17:17,738
BARNEY: Oh, no.
We're about to
get in a fight,

385
00:17:17,804 --> 00:17:19,614
and I can't run away.

386
00:17:19,672 --> 00:17:20,942
ROBIN:
I can't take my clothes off.

387
00:17:21,007 --> 00:17:23,137
It's freezing up here.
I'd get hypothermia.

388
00:17:23,210 --> 00:17:24,880
Maybe I can jump it?

389
00:17:24,944 --> 00:17:26,214
Maybe just my pants?

390
00:17:29,482 --> 00:17:31,252
This no-fighting
thing is over, huh?

391
00:17:32,519 --> 00:17:35,119
I think so.

392
00:17:35,188 --> 00:17:35,988
How could you possibly...
I can't believe...

393
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:37,255
...agree with Lily?
...that you made Lily

394
00:17:37,324 --> 00:17:39,434
get in a fight about this!
She's shorter than him!

395
00:17:39,492 --> 00:17:42,162
And it didn't end there.
We've been fighting
ever since.

396
00:17:42,229 --> 00:17:44,859
All those fights
we kept not having,
they all came back around.

397
00:17:44,931 --> 00:17:46,031
The bag of panties.

398
00:17:46,099 --> 00:17:47,429
The tie Robin murdered.

399
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:50,100
The tiny camera
I found in
the headboard.

400
00:17:50,170 --> 00:17:52,870
That's how a quarterback
stays sharp.

401
00:17:52,939 --> 00:17:55,609
Monday morning,
he sits on a bag of ice
and studies the game tape.

402
00:17:55,675 --> 00:17:57,435
Barney,
for the millionth...
You don't get to be...

403
00:17:57,510 --> 00:17:58,480
...using
football analogies...
...as good as I am...

404
00:17:58,545 --> 00:17:59,505
...and studying
technique!

405
00:17:59,579 --> 00:18:01,609
...does not make it
any less creepy.

406
00:18:01,681 --> 00:18:04,781
I knew it! I knew
you guys were acting
too cute and perfect.

407
00:18:04,851 --> 00:18:07,821
Look, we were just sick
of everyone pointing out

408
00:18:07,887 --> 00:18:10,617
how crappy
at relationships
we both are.

409
00:18:10,690 --> 00:18:13,190
Yeah, it was sort of nice
to be the perfect couple
for a minute.

410
00:18:13,260 --> 00:18:14,630
TED: I knew you were lying.

411
00:18:14,694 --> 00:18:17,604
You got to wake up
pretty early to
slip one by the T-Mose.

412
00:18:17,664 --> 00:18:18,604
Stop it.

413
00:18:20,467 --> 00:18:23,337
(LILY IN SING-SONG TONE)
Marshall, dinner's ready.

414
00:18:23,403 --> 00:18:26,073
