447
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:56,260
I guess we got to
start talking more
and get into the real stuff.

448
00:19:56,329 --> 00:19:58,999
Yeah. Or there's a bench
in the elevator.

449
00:19:59,065 --> 00:20:00,525
That's better.

450
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:03,240
Hey, so what if we're not
the best couple in the world?

451
00:20:03,303 --> 00:20:05,203
Totally.
It's not a competition.
No.

452
00:20:05,272 --> 00:20:06,672
We win!

453
00:20:06,739 --> 00:20:08,009
Best couple
in the world!

454
00:20:08,074 --> 00:20:09,114
Whoo!

455
00:20:09,175 --> 00:20:09,975
Yeah!

456
00:20:14,213 --> 00:20:18,353
Guess what?
These glasses
are plastic.

457
00:20:18,418 --> 00:20:20,648
So we can just
throw them away.

458
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:23,620
That means no dirty
dishes in the sink.

459
00:20:23,690 --> 00:20:27,730
You're dirty.
Maybe I should
leave you in the sink.

460
00:20:30,297 --> 00:20:32,827
OLDER TED:
And once that first argument
got worked out,

461
00:20:32,899 --> 00:20:36,769
all those other arguments,
well, they got better, too.

